{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":173208,"duration_api_ms":171642,"num_turns":18,"result":"I've explored the codebase thoroughly. Here's what I found about the current state:\n\n**Current behavior:** When an enrollment is cancelled (`cancelar_inscripcion`), `_promote_from_waitlist()` **immediately** creates an active enrollment for the first waitlisted student and notifies them. There's no 24h confirmation window — the student is auto-enrolled.\n\n**What the task requires:** Instead of auto-enrolling, the system should:\n1. Notify the first waitlisted student that a spot opened\n2. Give them 24h to confirm\n3. If they don't confirm within 24h, move to the next person\n4. Repeat until someone confirms or the waitlist is exhausted\n\nHere's my first clarifying question:\n\n**How should the 24h timeout be enforced?** The project currently has no background task system (no Celery, no APScheduler). The options are:\n\n- **(A) Lazy evaluation** — Check expiration on-demand (when the student tries to confirm, when anyone views the waitlist, or when the next cancellation happens). No background workers needed. Simple, but the spot stays \"reserved\" until something triggers the check.\n- **(B) Background scheduler** — Add APScheduler or similar to run periodic checks (e.g., every 5 minutes) for expired offers. More responsive, but adds infrastructure.\n- **(C) FastAPI BackgroundTasks** — Schedule a deferred check at the exact 24h mark using `asyncio` (e.g., `asyncio.create_task` with `asyncio.sleep(86400)`). Lightweight but doesn't survive server restarts.\n\nWhich approach do you prefer, or should I recommend one?","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2d9e7df1-c7e6-4f4e-af8d-041617ced581","total_cost_usd":0.6543479000000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":13,"cache_creation_input_tokens":37169,"cache_read_input_tokens":227217,"output_tokens":2631,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_